<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F055DD75-7EE2-449F-9F9D-F0088140BD48" class="Actinopterygii" family="Hemiodontidae" genus="Hemiodus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemiodus Müller 1842:206" order="Characiformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
Hemiodus 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Müller">Mueller</normalizedToken>
</taxonomicName>
, 1842, the largest genus in the Hemiodontidae, contains 18 species that occur in basins of Cis-Andean South America, including the Amazonas, Orinoco, Tocantins, costal rivers of the Guianas, some smaller independent drainages from the rio Araguari to the rio 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Paranaíba">Paranaiba</normalizedToken>
, and the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Paraná-Paraguay">Parana-Paraguay</normalizedToken>
basin (Langeani, 2003). Species of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F055DD75-7EE2-449F-9F9D-F0088140BD48" class="Actinopterygii" family="Hemiodontidae" genus="Hemiodus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemiodus Müller 1842:206" order="Characiformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hemiodus</taxonomicName>
are clearly separated from all other members of the family by the presence of multicuspid teeth with an enlarged convex distal border (vs. teeth absent in 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Hemiodontidae" genus="Anodus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Anodus</taxonomicName>
; unicuspid, pedicellated in 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:C88253F4-D8DC-41E0-8BF8-222818321390" class="Actinopterygii" family="Hemiodontidae" genus="Micromischodus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Micromischodus Roberts 1971:4" order="Characiformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Micromischodus</taxonomicName>
; tricuspid in 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:C6F1D762-2AAD-4364-B5C8-D2800760268A" class="Actinopterygii" family="Hemiodontidae" genus="Argonectes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Argonectes Böhlke &amp; Myers 1956:2" order="Characiformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Argonectes</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:BDFF6B31-31AB-47AC-B652-EB5D0D14DAC3" class="Actinopterygii" family="Hemiodontidae" genus="Bivibranchia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Bivibranchia Eigenmann 1912:253, 258" order="Characiformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Bivibranchia</taxonomicName>
). 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F055DD75-7EE2-449F-9F9D-F0088140BD48" class="Actinopterygii" family="Hemiodontidae" genus="Hemiodus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemiodus Müller 1842:206" order="Characiformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hemiodus</taxonomicName>
species also present a right angle depression on the ventromedial portion of the preopercle which receives the posteroventral portion of the hyomandibular (Langeani, 1998, 1999).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
